ce:section.ce:para:
3-(6-Hydroxyl) hexyloxy phthalonitrile was synthesized using the procedure described in a previous study [48]. α Nitrophthalonitrile (0.5 g, 2.8 mmol), 1,6-hexanediol (6.8 mL, 57.6 mmol) and dry potassium carbonate (4.5 g, 32.6 mmol) were added to dry N,N-dimethylformamide (35 mL). The mixture was stirred at room temperature for 48 h under nitrogen flow. Then, the reaction mixture was poured into ice-water (200 mL) and was obtained by suction filtration. Finally, the light-yellow product was crystallized from ethyl acetate. yield: 1.3 g (46.4%). EI-MS found (calcd): 244.1 (245.1). IR (KBr, cm−1): 3400 (OH); 2927 (Ar-H); 1649 (CN); 1323, 1266 (CH2
                           ); 1588, 1487, 1407 (CC); 1282 (Ar-O-C). 1H NMR (DMSO‑d
                           6, 400 MHz). ppm 7.5–8.0 (t, 3H aromatics), 4.3 (s, 1H, O–H), 1.0–4.2 (m, 12H, CH2). Elemental analysis (MW 369.3): C14H16N2O2 found (calcd): C 69.2% (68.8%); H 6.2% (6.6%); N 11.8% (11.5%); O 12.8% (13.1%).
